SOP: Dust Collector High Differential Pressure and Bag Leakage

1. Notify utility area supervisor and environmental monitoring desk.
2. Monitor the baghouse differential pressure (dP) and stack opacity readings on SCADA.
3. If dP exceeds 180 mm H2O or opacity exceeds 10%, prepare for immediate isolation.
4. Set the pulse-jet controller to continuous offline cleaning mode to clear filter bags.
5. If dP does not drop, perform LOTO on the exhaust fan and isolate the compartment.
6. Open the access hatch and perform visual inspection (or blacklight dye test) to identify torn bags.
7. Replace damaged filter bags with spare Nomex media bags and secure the snap bands.
8. Inspect hopper rotary valve operation and clear any bridged dust or build-up.
9. Verify compressed air supply pressure is steady at 6.0 bar and solenoids are firing correctly.
10. Close access hatches, remove LOTO, restart exhaust fan, and confirm dP is below 120 mm H2O.
